    {
      "id": 12, "type": "Note", "pos": [40, -250], "size": [900, 210], "flags": {}, "order": 11, "mode": 0,
      "properties": { "text": "" },
      "widgets_values": ["MASKED SUBJECT + GLOBAL\n\nBuilds two palettes for a structured Ideogram 4 prompt.\n\n1) Right-click the Load Image node -> Open in MaskEditor and paint over the subject, then Save.\n2) Masked Extractor reads ONLY the masked pixels; Override clamps it to <=5 colors (Ideogram's per-element limit). That is the palette you paste into a compositional_deconstruction element's color_palette.\n3) Element Palette (middle) is the quick alternative - <=5 colors from the whole image, no mask.\n4) The standard Extractor + Palette->Global JSON produce the GLOBAL style_description palette.\n\nThere is intentionally no node that fabricates the full compositional_deconstruction block (it carries per-element desc/bbox you author) - this graph hands you the palettes ready to drop in. ShowText nodes are optional."],
      "color": "#432", "bgcolor": "#653", "title": "README"
    }
