  "config": {},
  "extra": {
    "note": "MASKED SUBJECT + GLOBAL: build a structured Ideogram 4 prompt with TWO palettes. Top row -- paint a mask over the subject (right-click the LoadImage -> Open in MaskEditor); the Masked Extractor reads only those pixels, then Override clamps to <=5 colors (Ideogram's per-element compositional_deconstruction limit). That region-accurate palette is what you paste into a compositional_deconstruction element's color_palette. The Element Palette node (middle) is the quick alternative -- it pulls <=5 colors from the whole image without a mask. Bottom row -- the standard Extractor + Palette->Global JSON produce the GLOBAL style_description palette. There is intentionally no node that fabricates the full compositional_deconstruction block (it carries per-element desc/bbox you author), so this graph hands you the two palettes ready to drop in. ShowText nodes are OPTIONAL (ComfyUI-Custom-Scripts)."
  },
